  "_comment": "Layer 5 demo — the classic 3C miss taxonomy (Hill 1989). Three caches, all 4 lines, fed the same access trace 0,4,8,12,16,0,4,8,12,16,... A direct-mapped cache shows mostly CONFLICT misses (multiple addrs map to the same line). A 4-line fully-associative cache shows mostly CAPACITY misses (5 unique addrs > 4-line budget). A larger fully-associative cache (8 lines) shows mostly COMPULSORY (cold-start) misses. Open the Pipeline panel CACHE (LIVE) section: each row shows the full hit/miss tally PLUS the 3C breakdown (compulsory / capacity / conflict).",
